The curriculum aims to provide students a basic knowledge in eye anatomy, physiology and function of vision. Practical training consists of the visual acuity and  the refraction measurements, of evaluation of the visual fields and color vision. Observation of the eyelids and eye movements. Observation of the eyeballs anterior and posterior parts with direct and indirect ophthalmoscopy. Recognition of disorders of the eyeball position and motility, reactions of the pupil.
Most important concepts of diagnosis and management of ocular disorders are provided with
special reference to general practice. During the practical course the teaching staff follows the students ability to recognize common eye diseases and their hallmarks in the patients. 
By the end of the course all students have to write a paper (in english in english language group) about one eye diseases or condition.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The curriculum aims to provide students a basic knowledge in eye anatomy and physiology, introduction to optics and optical correction. To introduce students common eye diseases and diagnostic methodology. Main approach is given to eye diseases in general medicine praxis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course student: -	knows ethiology and pathogenesis of the common eye diseases, connections of eye conditions with general diseases; -	is familiar with examination methods in ophthalmology; -	knows how to use basic examination tests, have an overview about instrumental ophthalmological tests and have ability to interpret main investigational methods in ophthalmology; -	has an overview of the ethiology and pathogenesis, is able to diagnose common eye diseases; -	is able to adjudge the clinical picture of eye diseases and its difficulty; -	knows the principles of treatment of eye diseases; -	has an overview about surgical treatment of eye diseases; -	is able to test visual acuity and measure refraction, knows the principles of optical correction.
